---
description: Git branch, commit, and PR conventions for solo GitHub projects
alwaysApply: true
---

# Branch naming
- Format: `<type>/<issue#>-<short-slug>` (e.g. `feat/42-resume-checkpointing`)
- Omit the issue number when no GitHub issue exists: `<type>/<short-slug>`
- Lowercase, hyphenated slug, no spaces.

# Commit & PR titles (Conventional Commits)
- Format: `<type>: <imperative description>` (e.g. `feat: add checkpoint-resume to training loop`)
- Do NOT put issue numbers in the title.
- Allowed types: feat, fix, refactor, perf, chore, docs, test, ci, build

# PR body
- When the PR resolves an issue, include a closing keyword: `Closes #<issue>`.
- This auto-closes the issue on merge to the default branch.

# When the user references a task by issue number, use that number in the branch name.
